notes: Carbon gets hit by a car. The driver didn't even stop. Zofia brings Carbi to the Mundo Mascota clinic in San Cristóbal. Dr. Juan José takes an X-ray. Comminuted fracture. Dr. Juan José says he is not able to operate on our dog and sends us to Tuxtla Gutierrez to Dr. Joe Miceli Fernandez, best doctor in Chiapas, one of the best in Mexico.
Carbi in the clinic in observation. Zofia making phone calls with the doctors: stool and urine are fine, his condition is stable, he will be operated tomorrow.
1st SURGERY: intramedullary pin and cerclage wiring installed plus outside fixture to immobilize the femur X-ray X-ray
Carbon in the clinic
Carbon in the clinic
Picked up Carbon from the clinic
Carbi at home
Dr. Marina came for house-call: suspected inflammation. Brought Carbon back to clinic to be checked. Pic1, Pic2, Pic3
Carbon in the clinic
Picked up Carbon from the clinic Pic1, Pic2, Pic3
Dr. Marina took out the drainage tube and removed the stitches
Checkup with Dr. Miceli, wound looking good, everything fine, next appointment in two weeks

Went to Dr. Marina's office office because we heard cracking noises in Carbon's leg. Carbi received 1 ml of Xilacina (Xylazine sold as Rompun by Bayer) to calm him for his X-ray. Even though he was sedated he still fought to not allow us to turn him on his back, which might have contributed to the leg noise becoming louder X-ray
Miceli didn't like the new fissure in the bone he saw in the X-ray; assistants took Carbon to the next room to inject him with a pain killer and Carbon fell off the table!
Carbi back at home, eating again after many days without appetite, still some clicking in the bone
Dr Miceli on holidays so concerned about the crackling sound in his leg we went to Mundo Mascota, Dr. Juan Jose's clinic, nice guy, didn't want payment for services, cut Carbon's nails

Checkup with Dr. Miceli, external fixation removed (it started moving on its own a bit), Got anesthesia (Ketamine) to take X-ray, bone looks good, muscles atrophied in front and contracted in back; Dr. Miceli told us how to start physiotherapy; week-1 therapy: 15 min warm the leg, 15 min knee-joint ROM, 15 min hip ROM; week-2 therapy: 15 min warming the leg, 30 min whole leg ROM X-ray
Started rehab
Started to be able to sit down (with the one leg still extended)
Rehab is so much better with cannabis
Carbon is starting to sit down from standing nicely
no rehab today

Checkup with Dr. Miceli; no rehab today; Skin cut open and because the pin moved up a bit the end was cut off and the skin stitched back up, for sure he received some anesthesia; we slept overnight in Tuxtla in the bus in the nice place down by the river X-ray
no rehab today
Rehab w/ knee still
Rehab w/ knee still
Stopped rehab with the joint and now just working the muscles
Miceli diagnosed Carbon with 'no union' and we scheduled PrP treatment for next week
Zofia made a mustard seed bag (instead of wet towels) to use for heating Carbon's leg
Dropped Carbon off for his Platelet-rich Plasma (PrP) treatment
2nd SURGERY: Installing the X-pins inside the femur on top of the intramedullary pin to immobilize the leg better.
He stayed in the clinic a little longer than expected due to excess inflammation X-ray X-ray
Picked Carbi up from Dr. Miceli with the screws installed
His pin started sticking out of the skin
Rolando stitched up the skin around the pin
Finished brewing our last batch of oil
Pin poked out of the skin again
The intramedullary pin moving. Dr. Miceli said we still need the pin so lets fix it with another screw
3rd SURGERY: Carbon got yet another screw installed to secure the intra-medular pin
Dr. Miceli said he wants him for longer observation to make sure the new pin doesn't move
Zofia photographed & sent xrays to Miceli so he can consult with his maestro about a possible solution
X-ray

3rd PrP, this time injected PrP

We continued with the muscle and joint physiotherapy at home
Checkup - Dr. Miceli: Everything looking great :)
Half rehab today: only muscle massage, no joint flexing
Checkup - Dr. Miceli: Looking good! :)
Steven brought a low-level laser device from the States (RIKTA Esmil 2A) and today Carbon started receiving his laser therapy. Tri-Flex is now replaced by TopDog supplement
Checkup - Dr. Miceli: The fracture is united! :) X-ray X-ray X-ray
Carbon started actually walking. Is the laser helping? :)
Zofia made a short movie for family and friends showing Carbon walking: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4l84EhFfagc
Alicia came over and gave Carbon Reiki & a Bach flower remedy
Checkup - Dr. Miceli: Soon we can schedule removal of the implant. Dr. Beremiz Sánchez will be coming from Mexico City to operate since he initially installed the implant. X-ray X-ray
5th SURGERY: Implant removal. All metal is out: center pin, plate, 7 screws

Picked up Carbi from the clinic. Dr. Miceli commented that the bone is strong and Carbi is using his leg now more then before and really pushing himself of the floor with it. Carbi got brought out from the back of the clinic by one of the assistants. When he saw us, he go a bit excited and tried to put his leg on the floor with more strenght and cried. We brought him home, the leg was dangling while he was walking. Zofia started massaging his leg a bit at home, he did not like it. While lifting his leg by the feet gently up, it was lifting from the middle of the femur and not from the hip. Zofia suspects a fracture.
Carbon not using his leg. Zofia still suspects a fracture.
Carbon occasionally crying while he is trying to lay down or get up.
Scheduled a visit for tomorrow to get his leg x-rayed.
Suspicion confirmed: 're-fracture' :( We are heartbroken :( X-ray
